&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Clinical Fellow in Pancreaticobiliary Medicine, fixed term 1 year beginning 1st March 2021&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The appointee will participate in the management of patients with pancreatic and biliary diseases through liaison with referring teams and triaging of referrals, performing ERCP and EUS under supervision, attending Multidisciplinary meetings for benign and malignant PB diseases. The post includes a contribution to the out-of-hours rota for hepatology and liver transplantation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is most suited to trainees at or near the end of training in gastroenterology and hepatology wishing to pursue a sub-specialist interest and to gain experience in ERCP and EUS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Dr Jonathan Potts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Consultant Hepatologist&lt;/p&gt;
